# Vercel Environment Variables Import Format
# Use this file to import environment variables into Vercel
# Dashboard → Settings → Environment Variables → "Add Another" → Or use Vercel CLI

# Instructions:
# 1. Deploy your backend to Render first (see RENDER_BACKEND_DEPLOYMENT.md)
# 2. Copy your Render backend URL (e.g., https://leetracker-backend-xxxx.onrender.com)
# 3. Replace the URL below with your actual backend URL
# 4. Go to Vercel Dashboard → Your Project → Settings → Environment Variables
# 5. Click "Add Another" and paste the line below, OR use vercel CLI:
#    vercel env add VITE_API_URL production

# Backend API URL (REQUIRED)
VITE_API_URL=https://leetracker-backend.onrender.com

# Note: After adding/updating environment variables in Vercel:
# 1. Go to Deployments tab
# 2. Click "..." on latest deployment
# 3. Click "Redeploy" to apply the changes
